<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 1384/93 of 4 June 1993 on the transport and sale of feed grain held by the Spanish intervention agency for disposal to stockfarmers established in certain regions of Portugal </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1384/93 Hispaania sekkumisameti valduses oleva s&ouml;&ouml;dateravilja veo ja m&uuml;&uuml;gi kohta Portugali teatavate piirkondade loomakasvatajatele 4. juuni 1993 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in cereals (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1738/92 (2), and in particular Article 7 (5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 teraviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1738/92, (2) eriti selle artikli 7 l&otilde;iget 5, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3492/90 of 27 November 1990 laying down the factors to be taken into consideration in the annual accounts for the financing of intervention measures in the form of public storage by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund, Guarantee Section (3), and in particular Article 1 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. novembri 1990. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3492/90, millega n&auml;hakse ette asjaolud, mida tuleb aastaaruannetes arvesse v&otilde;tta Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust riikliku ladustamisena rakendatavate sekkumismeetmete finantseerimiseks, (3) eelk&otilde;ige selle artiklit 1, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1581/86 of 23 May 1986 laying down general rules for intervention on the market in cereals (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2203/90 (5) provides that cereals held by the intervention agency are to be disposed of by invitation to tender; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 23. mai 1986. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1581/86 (millega s&auml;testatakse teraviljaturul sekkumise &uuml;ldeeskirjad, (4) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2203/90 (5)) artiklis 3 s&auml;testatakse, et sekkumisametite valduses olev teravili tuleb m&uuml;&uuml;a pakkumismenetluse teel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82 (6), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 966/93 (7), lays down the procedure and the conditions for the disposal of cereals held by intervention agencies; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82, (6) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 966/93, (7) s&auml;testatakse sekkumisametite valduses oleva teravilja m&uuml;&uuml;gi kord ja tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, as a result of the persisting drought, certain regions of Portugal are suffering from a severe shortage of fodder and feed grain; whereas this situation is a threat to stockfarmers, who, being unable to obtain supplies at a reasonable price, may be forced to sell their livestock prematurely; whereas appropriate action should be taken in order to avoid such negative consequences; </inglise>
<eesti> j&auml;tkuva p&otilde;ua tulemusena kannatavad Portugali teatavad piirkonnad t&otilde;sise s&ouml;&ouml;da- ja s&ouml;&ouml;dateraviljapuuduse all; selline olukord ohustab loomakasvatajaid, kes ei ole v&otilde;imelised hankima tarneid m&otilde;istliku hinnaga ning v&otilde;ivad seet&otilde;ttu olla sunnitud m&uuml;&uuml;ma oma karja enneaegselt; negatiivsete tagaj&auml;rgede v&auml;ltimiseks tuleks v&otilde;tta asjakohased meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Spain has large intervention stocks stored in regions other than those affected by the drought; whereas it is necessary to transport quantities of feed grain taken over by the Spanish intervention agency to the border regions of Portugal; whereas these reasons justify the approval of such transport at the lowest cost; </inglise>
<eesti> Hispaanial on suured sekkumisvarud, mis on ladustatud v&auml;ljaspool m&otilde;jutatud piirkondi; Hispaania sekkumisameti &uuml;lev&otilde;etud s&ouml;&ouml;dateraviljakogused tuleb vedada Portugali piirialadele; need p&otilde;hjused &otilde;igustavad k&otilde;ige v&auml;ikemate kuludega veo heakskiitmist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas stockfarming has been particularly affected by the drought; whereas the use of the cereals should therefore be limited to drought-stricken stockfarmers established in those regions; whereas all necessary measures must be taken by the Member State to monitor such use; </inglise>
<eesti> p&otilde;ud on eriti m&otilde;jutanud loomakasvatust; k&otilde;nealuse teravilja kasutamis&otilde;igus tuleks seet&otilde;ttu anda &uuml;ksnes asjaomaste piirkondade loomakasvatajatele, kes on p&otilde;ua t&otilde;ttu kannatanud; liikmesriik peab v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik sellise kasutuse j&auml;relevalveks vajalikud meetmed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a security must be put up to guarantee the performance of the operation; </inglise>
<eesti> toimingu tegemise tagamiseks tuleb esitada tagatis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the provision of feed grain is insufficient to resolve the existing difficulties facing stockfarmers; whereas, in view of the special circumstances, deferred payment for cereals purchased should be permitted; </inglise>
<eesti> loomakasvatajate olemasolevate probleemide lahendamiseks ei piisa s&ouml;&ouml;dateravilja hankimisest; eriliste asjaolude t&otilde;ttu tuleks lubada ostetud teravilja eest tasumise edasil&uuml;kkamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Cereals, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las teraviljaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Portuguese intervention agency, hereinafter called the INGA, shall, under the conditions laid down in Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82, issue a standing invitation to tender for the resale of 60 000 tonnes of barley held by the Spanish intervention agency, hereinafter called the Senpa, with a view to disposal to drought-stricken stockfarmers in the Portuguese regions of Alentejo, Beira interior e Tras-os-Montes, the eastern half of Entre Douro e Minho, Beira Litoral and Ribatejo Oeste and the northern half of the Algarve. </inglise>
<eesti> Portugali sekkumisamet (edaspidi INGA) kuulutab m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82 s&auml;testatud tingimuste kohaselt v&auml;lja alalise pakkumismenetluse Hispaania sekkumisameti (edaspidi SENPA) valduses oleva 60 000 tonni odra edasim&uuml;&uuml;giks p&otilde;ua t&otilde;ttu kannatanud loomakasvatajatele j&auml;rgmistes Portugali piirkondades: Alentejo, Beira interior e Tras-os-Montes, Entre Douro e Minho idaosa, Beira Litoral ja Ribatejo Oeste ning Algarve p&otilde;hjaosa. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82, the following special rules shall apply to this invitation to tender: </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82 s&auml;tete kohaldamist, kohaldatakse k&otilde;nealuse pakkumismenetluse puhul j&auml;rgmisi erieeskirju: </eesti>
<inglise> - the cereals shall be disposed of by invitation to tender at the silos of the storehouses in the border regions of the provinces of Badajoz or Salamanca, </inglise>
<eesti> - teravili m&uuml;&uuml;akse pakkumismenetluse teel Badajozi v&otilde;i Salamanca ringkondade piirialadel asuvate hoidlate silodes, </eesti>
<inglise> - only stockfarmers in the Portuguese regions listed in paragraph 1 or their authorized agents may submit tenders, </inglise>
<eesti> - pakkumisi v&otilde;ivad esitada &uuml;ksnes l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud Portugali piirkondade loomakasvatajad v&otilde;i nende volitatud esindajad, </eesti>
<inglise> - tenders shall refer to the actual quantity of the consignment for which the tender is being made and submitted to the INGA, which shall forward them to the Senpa, </inglise>
<eesti> - pakkumised k&auml;sitlevad pakkumise aluseks oleva partii tegelikku kogust ja need esitatakse INGAle, kes edastab need SENPAle, </eesti>
<inglise> - the security referred to in the second indent of Article 13 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82 shall not apply, </inglise>
<eesti> - m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82 artikli 13 l&otilde;ike 4 teises taandes osutatud tagatist ei kohaldata, </eesti>
<inglise> - the tender selected must be at least 95 % of the intervention price referred to in Article 7 of Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75, applicable on the closing date for submission of tenders; however, for tenders submitted from 1 June, the intervention price to be taken into account shall be that for May, </inglise>
<eesti> - vastuv&otilde;etav pakkumine peab vastama v&auml;hemalt 95 protsendile m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 artiklis 7 osutatud sekkumishinnast, mida kohaldatakse pakkumiste esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;eval; alates 1. juunist esitatud pakkumiste puhul v&otilde;etakse arvesse mais kohaldatavat sekkumishinda, </eesti>
<inglise> - a security equal to the intervention price must be lodged with INGA by the successful tenderer to guarantee payment for the awarded cereals; the security shall be released on payment; Article 17 (1) and the second indent of Article 17 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82 shall apply mutatis mutandis, </inglise>
<eesti> - edukas pakkuja peab pakkumisega h&otilde;lmatud teravilja eest tasumise tagamiseks esitama INGAle sekkumishinnaga v&otilde;rdse tagatise; teravilja eest maksmisel tagatis vabastatakse; m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82 artikli 17 l&otilde;iget 1 ja artikli 17 l&otilde;ike 4 teist taanet kohaldatakse mutatis mutandis, </eesti>
<inglise> - the closing date for submission of tenders shall be 18 June 1993, </inglise>
<eesti> - pakkumise esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;ev on 18. juuni 1993, </eesti>
<inglise> - INGA shall guarantee to Senpa payment for the cereals awarded and removed. </inglise>
<eesti> - INGA tagab SENPAle edukate pakkumistega h&otilde;lmatud ja &auml;raviidud koguste eest tasumise. </eesti>
<inglise> Payment shall be made not later than the tenth day following the deadline for payment laid down in Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Maksmine toimub hiljemalt k&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast artiklis 2 s&auml;testatud makset&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first paragraph of Article 16 of Regulation (EEC) No 1836/82, payment for the awarded cereals shall be made by the successful tenderer to the Portuguese intervention agency not later than the end of the sixth month following the month in which the contract was awarded. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1836/82 artikli 16 esimesest l&otilde;igust, peab edukas pakkuja pakkumismenetluse teel m&uuml;&uuml;dud teravilja eest tasuma Portugali sekkumisametile hiljemalt lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kuule j&auml;rgneva kuuenda kuu l&otilde;puks. </eesti>
<inglise> The latter must pay the Spanish intervention agency the equivalent of all the amounts received in pesetas, on the basis of the exchange rate calculated using the relationship between the value of the ecu in both of the currencies concerned, as published in the Official Journal of the European Communities on the day following the invitation to tender. </inglise>
<eesti> Portugali sekkumisamet peab Hispaania sekkumisametile maksma vastuv&otilde;etud summadele vastava summa peseetades, v&otilde;ttes aluseks kursi, mille arvutamisel on arvesse v&otilde;etud asjaomaste v&auml;&auml;ringute ja ek&uuml;&uuml; kursside suhet, mis avaldatakse Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas pakkumismenetluse v&auml;ljakuulutamisele j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The quantities of barley awarded shall be made available to successful tenderers by Senpa without delay. </inglise>
<eesti> SENPA teeb lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud odrakogused edukatele pakkujatele viivitamata k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise> Senpa shall be responsible for the transport of the cereals from the place of storage to the place of disposal. </inglise>
<eesti> SENPA vastutab teravilja veo eest ladustuskohast m&uuml;&uuml;gikohta. </eesti>
<inglise> This shall be approved in accordance with Article 1 of Regulation (EEC) No 3492/90. </inglise>
<eesti> See kiidetakse heaks vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3492/90 artiklile 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) shall reimburse transport costs to Senpa up to ECU 20 per tonne plus, where necessary, the costs of additional entries and removals. </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfond h&uuml;vitab SENPAle veoarvete esitamisel veokulud kuni 20 ek&uuml;&uuml; ulatuses tonni kohta ning vajaduse korral t&auml;iendavad ladustamise ja laost v&auml;ljaviimise kulud. </eesti>
<inglise> The INGA shall reimburse Senpa for any additional transport costs exceeding the abovementioned limit, on presentation of transport invoices. </inglise>
<eesti> INGA h&uuml;vitab SENPAle veoarvete esitamisel k&otilde;ik t&auml;iendavad veokulud, mis &uuml;letavad eespool nimetatud piirsumma. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Portuguese authorities shall take the necessary steps to guarantee the performance of the operation and inform the Commission of them. </inglise>
<eesti> Portugali ametiasutused v&otilde;tavad toimingu tegemise tagamiseks vajalikud meetmed ja teavitavad nendest komisjoni. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Senpa shall show the operation in the accounts provided for by Regulation (EEC) No 3492/90. </inglise>
<eesti> SENPA kannab toimingu m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 3492/90 s&auml;testatud aruandesse. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Successful tenderers must be prepared to undergo all the checks which INGA may wish to carry out in order to assure itself that the tenderer is actually a stockfarmer or an authorized representative. </inglise>
<eesti> Edukad pakkujad peavad l&auml;bima k&otilde;ik kontrollid, mida INGA soovib teha veendumaks, et pakkuja on loomakasvataja v&otilde;i volitatud esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 4 June 1993. </inglise>
